Interface ExtraInputHandler

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ActionListener, EventListener
    All Known Implementing Classes:

    public interface ExtraInputHandler
extends ActionListener
    This interface extends ActionListener but also demands a process-method from the implementing class.

    mikkotiainen

    • Method Detail

      • process

        void process(String input)
        This is supposed to be a method that can be called by a secondary input to prompt the implementing class to process that input. This class was meant to be used in conjuction with the InputWindow-class that pops-up an additional input query.
        Parameters:
        input - The input to be processed (from the secondary input source, i.e. InputWindow).
